    <briefdescription>
<para>Scale-and-saturate float-to-UQ15 (offset-binary uint16) converter. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Converts a normalised float sample in [-1, +1] to offset-binary uint16 (UQ15 format): the Q15 quantised value is shifted by +32768 so that -1.0 maps to 0, 0.0 maps to 32768, and +1.0 maps to 65535.</para>
<para>Encoding: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">v_Q15<sp/>=<sp/>round(x<sp/>*<sp/>scale);<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Q15<sp/>in<sp/>[-32768,<sp/>32767]</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">u<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>(uint16_t)((int32_t)v<sp/>+<sp/>32768);<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>UQ15<sp/>in<sp/>[0,<sp/>65535]</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>The <computeroutput>clipped</computeroutput> flag is set whenever the pre-saturation scaled value falls outside [-32768, 32767]. It is sticky — cleared only by reset().</para>
<para>Lifecycle: create -&gt; (step / steps / reset)* -&gt; destroy</para>
<para>Example: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structf32__to__uq15__state__t" kindref="compound">f32_to_uq15_state_t</ref><sp/>*obj<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="f32__to__uq15__core_8h_1abeacf9743e990b963a7773e9b9abb9ca" kindref="member">f32_to_uq15_create</ref>(32768.0f);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint16_t<sp/>y<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="f32__to__uq15__core_8h_1a46ac0f0ba08d654ba7a96771e4bdba8b" kindref="member">f32_to_uq15_step</ref>(obj,<sp/>0.0f);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>y<sp/>==<sp/>32768</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint16_t<sp/>z<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="f32__to__uq15__core_8h_1a46ac0f0ba08d654ba7a96771e4bdba8b" kindref="member">f32_to_uq15_step</ref>(obj,<sp/>-1.0f);<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>z<sp/>==<sp/>0</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="f32__to__uq15__core_8h_1a7117c9b29e8ce79143e80e4671645e0a" kindref="member">f32_to_uq15_destroy</ref>(obj);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
